items.name: Melbourne-Housing-Price-Prediction-App
items.description: This project is a web application that predicts house prices based on user inputs such as the number of rooms, location, property type, and other key features. The model was trained using XGBoost, a cutting-edge machine learning algorithm, and deployed using Streamlit, a lightweight framework for creating interactive web applications.

items.name: ModelingToolkit.jl
items.description: An acausal modeling framework for automatically parallelized scientific machine learning (SciML) in Julia. A computer algebra system for integrated symbolics for physics-informed machine learning and automated transformations of differential equations

items.name: Image-Classification-Model
items.description: This is an Image classification Model that classifies the images as the categories of the dataset is trained on. This is a Machine Learning Model that uses Keras library under Tensorflow Framework.

items.name: brpc

items.name: ryzen-ai-documentation
items.description: Onboarding documentation source for the AMD Ryzen AI Software Platform.   The AMD Ryzen AI Software Platform enables developers to take pretrained machine learning models in popular frameworks and run them on laptops powered by AMD Ryzen AI technology.

items.name: sagemaker-distribution
items.description: A set of Docker images that include popular frameworks for machine learning, data science and visualization.

items.name: NewsTrader-AI
items.description: NewsTrader AI is an advanced system leveraging a multi-agent framework to predict stock prices based on news analysis. The project utilizes open-source large language models (LLMs) for fine-tuning and cutting-edge frontier LLMs for retrieval-augmented generation (RAG), combining traditional machine learning methods.

items.name: OpenPyStruct
items.description: Open-source toolkit that provides finite element model based optimization frameworks for generating training data and machine learning models for global structural optimization of indeterminate continuous structures

items.name: A-Machine-Learning-Approach-to-Optimize-Stroke-Prediction-Integrating-SMOTE-and-Random-Forest
items.description: This study has developed a comprehensive ma- chine learning framework that integrates the Synthetic Minority Over-sampling Technique (SMOTE) with Random Forest to address the class imbalance and improve predictive accuracy.

items.name: Ai-based-crop-prediction
items.description: This project uses machine learning to predict crop yield based on soil and environmental parameters. It provides farmers with data-driven recommendations for fertilizer use, optimizing yield and promoting sustainable agriculture. Built using Python, Django frameworks and machine learning algorithms like XGBoost and  Random Forest.
